At the top, I’ve placed ARK and numismatic collection. In details, I’ve placed provenance, artist, and loan information.

Other notes / questions
* While making this wireframe I also addressed R006, dropping Find fields below Obverse fields. Let me know if this should be a separate issue.
* I created a fictionalized coin with all of these fields, since there is no coin that contains all of them. Let me know if I should make multiple real coins when presenting the wireframes.
* I spoke with Eliot, and his main concern was provenance info (and dollars) being displayed. When publishing this data for Nomisma, Alan didn’t seem too concerned. I’ve included it here, but it will likely warrant a larger discussion.
* Should I have been more inventive? There’s quite a big difference between the two examples: our old website and ANS, so I played it safe.
* I would imagine that despite these changes, Alan may have some strong opinions about the order and grouping we decide on. Should we just provide a list of all fields and ask him to sort and group as he sees fit? Has that already been done?
